text: The John Young House is located in Muscoda, Wisconsin. ==History== John Young was a German immigrant who served in the American Civil War and worked as a lumber dealer. The house has since been turned into an antique store. It was added to the State and the National Register of Historic Places in 1994. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Houses in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Queen Anne architecture in Wisconsin
